{"type":"message","id":"a2af7fbb","parentId":"c9e177be","timestamp":"2026-02-14T07:07:52.768Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the top 3 \"Gold Standard\" GitHub repositories for each of your requested categories:\n\n### 1. Lightweight VPS Monitoring for Python Bots\n*Focus: Docker-compose support, auto-restart capabilities, and Telegram alerts.*\n\n1.  **[ArtCC/linux-server-admin-bot](https://github.com/ArtCC/linux-server-admin-bot)**\n    *   **Why:** A dedicated Telegram bot designed specifically for managing and monitoring Linux servers. It includes native support for Docker container management (start/stop/restart) and resource monitoring directly through a Telegram interface, making it perfect for bot owners.\n2.  **[pohape/self-hosted-tg-alerts-uptime-monitor](https://github.com/pohape/self-hosted-tg-alerts-uptime-monitor)**\n    *   **Why:** A Python-based, self-hosted uptime monitor that sends alerts via Telegram. It’s highly lightweight and focuses on verifying service health (GET/POST/SSL), which is essential for ensuring your bots are responsive and certificates are valid.\n3.  **[Gyalecta/python-system-watchdog](https://github.com/Gyalecta/python-system-watchdog)**\n    *   **Why:** A \"dockerized\" system monitoring agent. It tracks CPU, RAM, and Disk usage in real-time. It’s ideal for VPS environments where you need to ensure your Python bots aren't hitting resource ceilings that could cause silent failures.\n\n---\n\n### 2. MCP (Model Context Protocol) & Productivity Tools\n*Focus: Tools that bridge LLMs with file operations, data sources, and automated workflows.*\n\n1.  **[tadata-org/fastapi_mcp](https://github.com/tadata-org/fastapi_mcp)**\n    *   **Why:** The standard for Python developers wanting to turn existing APIs into MCP tools. It allows you to expose FastAPI endpoints as MCP tools with built-in authentication, enabling AI agents (like Claude or Cursor) to securely interact with your custom backends.\n2.  **[IBM/mcp-context-forge](https://github.com/IBM/mcp-context-forge)**\n    *   **Why:** A robust \"Gateway & Registry\" for MCP. It acts as a central management point for tools, resources, and prompts. This is the \"Get Shit Done\" tool for enterprise-grade context management, supporting Docker and Kubernetes deployments.\n3.  **[appcypher/awesome-mcp-servers](https://github.com/appcypher/awesome-mcp-servers)**\n    *   **Why:** While a list, it is the *de facto* gold standard for discovery. It categorizes the best official and community-built MCP servers (including file-op tools, browser automation, and DB connectors), saving you hours of research time.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Python Pre-deploy Checklists & Actions\n*Focus: Automated error prevention and standardizing CI/CD for Python projects.*\n\n1.  **[pre-commit/pre-commit-hooks](https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit-hooks)**\n    *   **Why:** The industry standard for \"shifting left.\" It ensures code never even reaches the repo if it fails basic checks (syntax, trailing whitespace, large files). It's the first line of defense for Python error prevention.\n2.  **[python-semantic-release/python-semantic-release](https://github.com/python-semantic-release/python-semantic-release)**\n    *   **Why:** Automates the entire release process including version bumping and changelog generation based on commit messages. It prevents \"human error\" during deployment and ensures your Python package metadata is always consistent.\n3.  **[astral-sh/ruff-action](https://github.com/astral-sh/ruff-action)**\n    *   **Why:** Ruff is the fastest Python linter and formatter. Using this official GitHub Action provides near-instant feedback on code quality, replacing Flake8, Isort, and Black in a single, high-performance step that is essential for modern Python CI workflows.","textSignature":"EjQKMgG+Pvb7H04uvueMY4HzIqr4npnjT2W/Tnj7cIGwWgMA7aHfsEfx1Oaany/vmN2G5gTX"}],"api":"google-generative-ai","provider":"google","model":"gemini-3-flash-preview","usage":{"input":37718,"output":903,"cacheRead":32579,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38621,"cost":{"input":0.018859,"output":0.002709,"cacheRead":0.00162895,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02319695}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771052865772}}
